<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Communist Party of Nepal Elects Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 1 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth National Congress
of the Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxism-Leninism, CPN-UML)
Sunday reelected Man Mohan Adhikari and Madhav Kumar Nepal as the
party's president and general-secretary, Radio Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
The congress, held in the mid-western city of Nepalgunj, also
chose 27 of the 35 Central Committee members.
</P>
<P>
The party's minority faction headed by former deputy prime
minister Bam Dev Gautam did not contest the elections for the
Central Committee following the defeat of their political report
and tactical line in the congress.
</P>
<P>
The congress approved the political and working policy
documents presented by the majority faction led by Madhav Kumar
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The congress, which opened on January 25, reaffirmed its faith
in the people's multiparty democracy, which was espoused by the
party's fifth national congress in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The congress also adopted an amended party statute.
</P>
<P>
The CPN-UML now is the largest party in parliament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
