<HEADLINE> Beira Corridor Business Council to Be Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 1 (Xinhua) -- A protocol on forming the Beira
Development Corridor Business Council which aims to promote
trade, investment and employment will be signed in Mozambique on
Monday, the Zimbabwe News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Among other objectives, the council will increase
communication among the business communities of the Beira
Development Corridor (BDC) and their governments.
</P>
<P>
It will also strengthen and promote the integration of the
business communities of the BDC.
</P>
<P>
The BDC is a railway and road network running between the
Zimbabwean eastern border town of Mutare to the Mozambican port
city of Beira.
</P>
<P>
The corridor was established last year after a two-day
conference held in Zimbabwe in 1996 at which Malawi, Mozambique,
Zambia and Zimbabwe signed the agreement for establishment of the
corridor.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing the low levels of investment and trade and the
resultant socio-economic problems within the region, the business
communities in Mozambique and Zimbabwe agreed to the formation of
BDC business council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
