<DOCNO> XIE19980202.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets with Swiss President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, Switzerland, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese
Vice Premier met here today with Swiss President Flavio Cotti on
the occasion of the annual meeting of the World Economic Forum.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the relationship between China and Switzerland has
been kept in a momentum of development. Frequent exchanges of
visits of the leaders of the two countries have enhanced mutual
understanding and have played an unreplaceable role in promoting
the overall development of the relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries also have developed smooth
cooperative relations in economy and trade, with trade values
going up continuously and Swiss companies spreading all over
China.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that China puts great emphasis on developing
relationship with Switzerland and gives a high appraisal to the
Swiss government for its constant observance of the one-China
policy.
</P>
<P>
"There is no controversy between China and Switzerland. We have
identical or similar views to many of the international affairs,"
Li said.
</P>
<P>
There are still lots of potentials for the two sides to
cooperate in trade and economy, Li went on.
</P>
<P>
"China will make efforts together with Switzerland towards the
development of a lasting and stable relationship of friendship and
cooperation," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Cotti spoke highly of the relationship between Switzerland and
China, saying that the two countries have been enjoying an
ever-growing cooperative relationship in all aspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
