<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Meets with WTO Director-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, Switzerland, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier
Li Lanqing met here today with World Trade Organization (WTO)
Director-General Renato Ruggiero on the occasion of the annual
meeting of the World Economic Forum.
</P>
<P>
Li explained China's stand on its entry into the multilateral
trade system and thanked Ruggiero for his support in this issue.
</P>
<P>
"Now that major progress has been made in recent negotiations,
we hope the issue will be solved as soon as possible," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Along with China's economic development, China's market will be
bigger and bigger, Li pointed out. The saying that China needs WTO
and WTO needs China has become a world cliche.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero said that the negotiations over China's accession have
made much progress. He believed that it is time to accelerate the
process.
</P>
<P>
He praised China for its "very positive attitude" to the
financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"We must encourage China to do that and we must be ready in the
negotiation with China to take the positive attitude that the
Chinese have shown to us now in order to speed up the
negotiation," the WTO head told Xinhua one day before his meeting
with the Chinese vice premier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
