<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Iran seized 1.5 tonnes of
morphine in the past two weeks in the central provinces of Yazd
and Kerman, local evening newspaper Resalat reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Sanee, provincial commander of Iran's Security Force
in Yazd, was quoted as saying that several smugglers were also
arrested in the actions.
</P>
<P>
