</P>
<P>
Sanee said about 11 tonnes of drugs have been confiscated in
Yazd province since March 21, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Iran is one of the key transit route of drugs from the infamous
Golden Crescent bordering Iran, Afghanistan and Pakistan. It
reportedly seizes an average of about 160 tonnes of different
narcotics each year.
</P>
<P>
To fight the serious social problem, Iran passed a strict
anti-drug law in 1989, under which anyone caught with 30 grams of
heroin or five kilograms of opium will face the death penalty.
