<HEADLINE> Primokov Reiterates Diplomatic Efforts in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian Minister of Foreign
Affairs Yevgeny Primakov today reiterated using diplomatic means
in the settlement of the Iraq crisis.
</P>
<P>
Primakov, who just returned from his tour of European capitals,
including Madrid, Brussels and Paris, told journalists that Russia
favors complete elimination of the Iraqi weapons of mass
destruction, but "this objective can be reached by diplomatic
means at present."
</P>
<P>
He said, "As concerns the situation around Iraq, it is
acquiring in ominous character, because we get more and more
information that a strike at Iraq can become a reality."
</P>
<P>
Russia believes that it could become a most serious blunder
which would entail many negative consequences capable of affecting
not only the region but also the entire system of international
relations, Primakov said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Russian special envoy Deputy Foreign Minister
Viktor Posuvalyuk left for Baghdad today on a new visit.
</P>
<P>
Before departure from Moscow, Posuvalyuk said Russia will try
again to persuade Iraq to make numerous concessions so as to avoid
a military conflict in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his French counterpart,
Jacques Chirac, today also had talks by telephone on the Iraq
situation. They insisted on the diplomatic way of overcoming the
crisis. 
</P>
