<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Banks Support Enterprise Reform in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The major banks in east China's
Anhui Province rendered greater support to state-owned enterprises
last year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The provincial branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of
China, the country's largest bank, increased its loans by 1.2
billion yuan to enterprises with which it has signed cooperative
agreements.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui branch of the Agricultural Bank of China, one of the
country's big-four state-owned commercial banks, selected 15
backbone enterprises as its major clients, extending to them a
total of 600 million yuan in loans for circulating funds and
technical renovation.
</P>
<P>
The local provincial branch of the Bank of China, China's
largest foreign exchange bank, granted 910 million yuan in loans
to key enterprises, which accounted for 90 percent of its annual
loan budget.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the provincial branch of the China Construction Bank
signed cooperative agreements with 19 enterprises and lent 80.7
percent of its new loans to key enterprises and major clients in
key industries.
</P>
<P>
Also last year the banks, together with the Bank of
Communications, wrote off 1.53 billion yuan in non-performing
loans owed by enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
