<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 130.44 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday gained 130.44 points to
3354.8 as against last weekend's close of 3224.36.
</P>
<P>
The national index also gained 53.45 points to 1454.83 as
against the previous close of 1401.38.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar indexes closed higher at 324.31 and
139.27 compared with the previous closes of 313.63 and 134.17
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Pivotals staged a sharp recovery on the BSE market Monday on
heavy bull support from leading financial institutions and
speculative buying from investors.
</P>
<P>
Even though foreign funds remained sidelined, local
institutions were inspired by a rally in the Hong Kong market
where the Hang Seng Index shot up by 14.3 percent.  
</P>
