<HEADLINE> Half of Chinese Take Trip In 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 660 million, or one
out of every two Chinese, traveled in 1997 to fuel the country's
booming tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China attracted 54 million overseas visitors and
earned 11.5 billion U.S. dollars from its fledging tourism sector.
</P>
<P>
Local observers said the country's tourism industry has
developed rapidly and the quality of local tourism services have
also been improved markedly.
</P>
<P>
A series of tourism promotions were launched last year,
which have helped attract more visitors, both domestic and
overseas, observers say.  
</P>
