<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Meets Chinese Vice Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Khin Nyunt said
here Monday that his country wants to further strengthen the
neighborly goodwill ties as well as trade and economic cooperation
with China.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with visiting Chinese Vice Minister of Foreign
Affairs Tang Jiaxuan here Monday, Khin Nyunt, first secretary of
the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council, said leaders of
the new generation of the two countries are responsible for
carrying on the good-neighborly and friendly ties forged by
leaders of the older generation.
</P>
<P>
Tang's visit will help enhance the development of trade and
economic cooperation between the two countries which have a great
potential, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Vice Minister Tang said China also attaches
importance to the development of Sino-Myanmar good-neighborly and
friendly relations and trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He is convinced that such relations would be continued and
further developed.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Tang also held talks with his Myanmar
counterpart, U Nyunt Swe, on the promotion of the two countries'
bilateral ties including trade and economic cooperation and on
matters of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice minister arrived here last Saturday on a
four-day visit to Myanmar at the invitation of U Nyunt Swe.
</P>
</TEXT>
