<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Guangxi Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region reported record high levels of exports
and overseas investment last year, according to deputy regional
chairman Zhang Wenxue.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Guangxi's exports rose 9.7
percent to 3.06 billion U.S. dollars in 1997, while its actual use
of overseas investment surged 23.5 percent to 1.26 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also last year, Guangxi registered a 117 percent increase in
its value of contractual overseas investment, with the total
amount reaching 1.47 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zhang attributed the significant growth in exports and overseas
investment to Guangxi's increased efforts to improve its
investment environment and open itself wider to other parts of the
world.
</P>
<P>
Since the early 1990s, Guangxi has increased its investment in
infrastructure such as transportation, telecommunication and
energy, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Guangxi has also taken effective measures to
improve the environment for overseas investors, such as
eliminating unreasonable fees and establishing specialized
agencies to deal with complaints.  
</P>
