Arab nations in the past as part of efforts to reactivate the
Middle East peace talks and also attended the U.S.-sponsored
Madrid talks between the Arab states and Israel in 1991.
</P>
<P>
He has always called on the Arab nations not to abandon peace
talks with Israel despite setbacks in the past two years since
hard-liner Benjamin Netanyahu became Israel's prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Argentina was one of the first nations to recognize Lebanon's
independence in 1945 and was quick to establish full diplomatic
ties.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that more than 1.2 million Argentineans are of
Lebanese origin, making the second largest Lebanese expatriates
community in South America after Brazil.
</P>
<P>
After visiting Lebanon, Menem will proceed to Egypt on February
4 where he is expected to inaugurate an Argentinean-built
non-military nuclear reactor worth 100 million
U.S. dollars. 
