<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
exported more than 2.4 billion U.S. dollars worth of machinery and
electronic products last year, up 28.9 percent over the previous
year, according to customs figures.
</P>
<P>
The amount, more than 40 percent of which was attributed to
high-tech products, represented 21.9 percent of the province's
total exports last year, up from 17 percent in 1995.
</P>
<P>
