<HEADLINE> Chicken Sales Near Normal in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 2 (Xinhua) -- The sales of chicken have come
near to the normal level over the past week, local chicken dealers
said.
</P>
<P>
Macao imported some 43,000 chickens over the past 10 days, and
sales have risen to about 4,000 a day, about the same in the
corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Va Kio newspaper said Monday that the rise of chicken sales
was the joint result of the Chinese Lunar New Year, the
announcement of Hong Kong to resume imports of chickens in
February, and the confirmation that no case of bird flu was
detected in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Hit by the fear of bird flu, imports of chickens plummeted to
about 500 a day in the worst time late last year. But the sales
gradually recovered in January.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that if current sales continue next week, the
sales of chicken will return to the normal level of about 7,000 a
day. That will mark the end of the fear of bird flu, it added.
</P>
</TEXT>
