<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine stock market soared
amid encouraging economic news for a second day Monday, with its
composite index jumping 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Investors, particularly foreigners, catapulted the market
higher because of recent favorable economic news and the peso's
steady gains over the past few days, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, the government announced that the country's
gross national product grew 5.8 percent last year, more than
predicted following Asia's financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share Philippine Stock Exchange composite index (Phisix)
surged 197.69 points to 2,145.70 while the broader all-shares
index gained 54.09 points to close at 622.12.
</P>
<P>
Total value turnover reached 4.6 billion pesos (109 million
U.S. dollars) while volume swelled to 2.14 billion shares.
</P>
<P>
With this, the Phisix has risen a stunning 441.63 points or
25.9 percent over the past six trading days.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the Phisix jumped 151.33 points, or 8.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Manila Electric Co., Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co.,
Ayala Land Inc., and Ayala Corp. are among the biggest gainers of
the day. 
