regarding the small miners, which he said was not conducive to
the growth of the industry.
</P>
<P>
While Zimbabwe was the third largest gold producer in Africa
after South Africa and Ghana, very little benefits had accrued to
the down stream industries, he said, adding only the buyer
countries benefited instead. 
