<HEADLINE> S. African Products Account for 28 Percent in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 2 (Xinhua) -- About 28 percent of all
products emanating from Africa are made by South Africa, local
daily Sowetan quoted a senior official as reporting Monday.
</P>
<P>
South Africa generates 50 percent of the power consumed in
Africa, and also accounts for 37 percent of the continent's
vehicles, Jan Visser, executive director of National Productivity
Institute told an Asian Productivity Organization symposium in
Tehran, Iran Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Visser said despite South Africa having only
5.5 percent of Africa's population, it generated 28 percent of
its products.
</P>
<P>
"In the African context, South Africa is well developed,
having a gross domestic product per capita of 14,760 Rand (2,952
U.S. Dollars) against 3,138 Rand (627 Dollars) for Africa, but in
the world context it is at best a developing country," Visser
said. 
</P>
