<HEADLINE> Chinese Enterprises Pool on Marketing Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Some Chinese enterprises have
pooled resources to establish a marketing network for themselves,
today's International Business Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Named Fudi, the marketing network, supported by large or
medium-sized backbone enterprises in about a hundred cities, has
been approved by the State Economic and Trade Commission to be an
experimental unit in the nation's products sales system.
</P>
<P>
The network has built a market place, 70 thousand square meters
in space, near the site of the Three Gorges, where the great
damming project relocated millions of people and created huge
demands. Fudi has also set up links among its members and
businesses in Asia-Pacific areas through its advanced satellite
communications system. The system provides various kinds of
industrial, commercial and service information on-line to
facilitate businesses.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guangwu, chief executive officer of Fudi, said the joint
establishment will be able to complish things that individual
enterprises can not do and the enterprises will complement each
other in competing with overseas companies. 
