<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen syndicates from 10
countries will vie for the renowned America's Cup yachting race in
New Zealand in 1999 and 2000, making the largest entry in the
history.
</P>
<P>
The Royal New Zealand Yacht Squadron grabbed the right to host
the cup after Team New Zealand, led by Sir Peter Blake, lifted it
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Following is the list of the confirmed challengers announced by
New Zealand's Sport and Tourism Minister Murray McCully on Monday:
</P>
<P>
Aberdeen Boat Club/Spirit of Hong Kong Challenge, Hong Kong,
China
</P>
<P>
Club Nautique Morgien/FAST 2000, Morges, Switzerland
</P>
<P>
Cortez Racing Association/Team Dennis Conner, San Diego, United
States
</P>
<P>
Cruising Yacht Club of Australia/Australian Challenge, Sydney,
Australia
</P>
<P>
Monte Real Club Yates de Bayona/Real Club Nautico de
Valencia/The Spanish Challenge, Madrid, Spain
