<HEADLINE> Farmers in Remote Area Get Clean Drinking Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, February 1 (Xinhua) -- More than 170,000 local farmers
from 40,000 rural families in Zunyi Prefecture, in southwestern
Guizhou Province now drink clean water because of a local
government program.
</P>
<P>
Zunyi was an old base of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
revolution against the Kuomintang in the 1930s-'40s. But local
farmers had no clean drinking water until last June, when the
program was launched by the local government with the help of the
Ministry of Water Resources.
</P>
<P>
Since June more than 16 million yuan has been invested to build
more than 13,000 water cellars.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials in charge of the project, each
household received 500 yuan from the government for digging the
water-pits.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, 80,000 more households, or 320,000
people, will have clean drinking water in the prefecture, the
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
