<HEADLINE> Samsonov Wins Euro Top 12 Table Tennis Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 1 (Xinhua) -- Vladimir Samsonov of Belarus
beat Swede Peter Karlsson in straight sets in the final to win the
European Top 12 table tennis competition in Halmstad, Sweden, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Samsonov scored an easy 21-12, 21-15 and 21-10 victory over
Karlsson, who grabbed the final spot by edging Belgian ace
Jean-Miche Saive in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Samsonov entered the final after beating Swede veteran Jan-Ove
Waldner 21-17, 16-21, 21-19, 21-16 in another semifinal.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, German Nicole Struse survived a seesaw
match of 21-13, 22-24, 16-21, 21-19, 21-16 against Luxemburg's Ni
Xia Lian to take the title.
</P>
<P>
In the earlier semifinals, Ni Xia Lian defeated Marie Svensson
fo Sweden while Struse beat Hungary's Csilla Batorfi.
</P>
<P>
Other competitors of the tournament, which attracted the top
elites of European table tennis, included French Jean Philippe
Gatien, Germany's Joerg Rosskopf, Sweden's Joegen Persson,
Greece's Kalinikos Kreanga, Austria's Werner Schlage, Italy's Yang
Min, Russian Dmitrij Mazunov and Romania's Vasile Florea.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event there were Jie Schoepp, Jing Tian-Zoerner
and Olga Nemes, all from Germany, Hungary's Krisztina Toth,
Russia's Irina Palina, Croatia's Tamara Boros and Romania's Otilia
Badescu and Italy's Alessia Arisi. 
</P>
