<HEADLINE> Malaysian Prime Minister to Visit Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad will pay a one-day visit to Manila Friday to
explore ways in reviving the economies of the two countries, the
local newspaper Today reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Philippine Department of Foreign Affairs were
quoted as saying Mahathir will hold talks with President Fidel
Ramos which will focus on the current currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda is the proposal made by the Philippine
government to set up a system that would allow the use of local
currencies in regional trade instead of the U.S. dollar, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
According to Philippine Foreign Affairs Secretary Domingo
Siazon, the government had ordered an interagency body to
formulate a scheme that would allow businessmen in Southeast Asia
to use the local currencies instead of U.S. dollars in trading
goods.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said Malaysia and Thailand would likely support the
Philippines on the proposed trading system.
</P>
<P>
But some businessmen are not enthusiastic about the idea
because the intra-ASEAN (the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations) is not too big to make a significant progress in
stabilizing their currencies.
</P>
<P>
Ramos and Mahathir could also discuss the regional security
that could be affected by the economic crisis, the report said.
</P>
