<HEADLINE> Shangdong Sets Record Transport Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 2 (Xinhua) -- Ports in east China's Shangdong
Province last year registered record-high transport volumes in
handling both cargo and passengers.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the local port administrations,
the cargo transport volume in major provincial ports totaled 115
million tons, a year-on-year growth of 12 percent. The containers
handled by these ports totaled 1.16 million units, up 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Also, all major airports increased frequency of flights to
foreign destinations.
</P>
<P>
In terms of passenger transport, the entry-exit volume was
520,000 last year, a rise of 18 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province last year posted a total trade volume of 13
billion U.S. dollars, up 11 percent. The foreign-funded ventures
registered a trade volume of 6.6 billion dollars, playing an
important part in Shandong's foreign trade.  
