<HEADLINE> East China Province Implements Help-the-Poor Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
implemented a Help-the-Poor Program to provide relief to the poor
people and assist unemployed factory workers in finding new jobs.
</P>
<P>
All prefectures and cities have set up special offices. So far,
nearly 30,000 local urban families living below the poverty line
have been brought under the government program.
</P>
<P>
Computers are being used in some areas to help investigate the
situation of urban poor families.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 percent of cities and counties have set up special
funds for the purpose, and have collected 43 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, nearly 200,000 families have received 37 million
yuan in relief funds from the government program.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has established 20 labor markets and
more than 1,300 job agencies. In 1997 alone, more than 100,000
laid-off factory workers had found new jobs, while 120,000 jobless
were employed. 
</P>
