<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Gaullist Movement Keeps Its Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 1 (Xinhua) -- France's Gaullist movement, the
Rally for the Republic (RPR), Sunday decided to keep its name
after a balloting at a party conference saw a majority of party
representatives prefer to change the name.
</P>
<P>
Philippe Seguin, the president of RPR, arbitrated to keep the
name of RPR, after 49.94 percent of the party representatives
voted for a change of the name into Rally for France.
</P>
<P>
Originally called Rally for the French People when the Gaullist
movement was created by President Charles De Gaulle in 1947, the
party had adopted several names before the RPR was founded by
Jacques Chirac in 1976. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
